hat applies left-padding formatting to create a 10-digit zero-padded result.\n\nNow I'm verifying the knowledge file structure against the source document. The source has 5 main sections, but the knowledge file splits into 9 sections, which is fine since they don't need to map 1:1. I'm checking whether large sections with subsections are properly split - the \"テーブルを使用した採番機能\" section is definitely over 2000 characters and has H3 subsections, and the knowledge file does split it across multiple entries, so that validation passes.\n\nI think the knowledge file is clean and ready. The XML examples and s8's code comments actually make the connection clear enough—showing how `SystemRepository.getObject()` uses the name attribute to retrieve the generator. While the knowledge file doesn't explicitly state this purpose, the implicit demonstration through code is sufficient for understanding why the name matters.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":21701,"cache_read_input_tokens":35069,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":21701,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":8},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"0bcd6507-f9b4-4dd3-b718-d48276f9ce27","uuid":"1705f13b-9992-44db-b3d4-64617ca8c1bb"}
